gather()wait()Inputcoroutines or taskstasks onlyReturnsordered list of results(done, pending) setsOn errorraises (or return_exceptions)you inspect each taskUse whenyou want all results in orderyou need partial results or FIRST_COMPLETED

5 — asyncio.sleep() — more than just waiting
pythonimport asyncio

async def main():
    # asyncio.sleep(0) — yields control to the event loop for one tick
    # Use it to let other tasks run without actually waiting
    async def cooperative_task(name, n):
        for i in range(n):
            print(f"{name}: step {i}")
            await asyncio.sleep(0)      # "yield" — let others run

